review_blob: 500mL bottle poured into a TeKu glass. ABV: 9%. Bright orange amber with medium to light head. Aromas reveal a beautifully balanced mix of pine, citrus and banana. The richly flavoured palate seamlessly combines pineapple, stone fruits and a big hit of bitterness. Powerful, long and beautifully balanced. Great beer.
beer_name: 4 Pines Keller Door Series Imperial IPA

review_blob: 330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent pack. Pale amber. Gorgeous fresh hoppy tropical aromas, loads of passionfruit and banana. Bold citrusy flavours follow, finishing with a zing of grapefruit bitterness. Great style and character.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent pack. Pale sandy gold and a white foamy head. Refreshing aromatics with citrus and tropical fruits. Flavours more subdued with chalky, straw and wheaty characters over a lemony backbone. Good summer drinking.

375mL can, BoozeBud Advent pack. Deep copper tones with substantial head, shining bright as it pours from the can. Great fresh citrusy aromas with passionfruit and pear in the mix. Delectable, well-defined flavours, bold, crisp, bitter, burnt caramel, a bit herbal and definitely spicy. An impressive brew.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent Pack. Pours deep copper brown with minimal head. Rich malty, toffee aromas, followed by malty, burnt caramel flavours with dark chocolate hints and moderate bitterness. Good depth but falls away a little at the finish. Interesting amber ale.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent Pack. Rich amber with foamy head and moderate carbonation. Refreshing piney resinous stonefruits aroma. Malty flavours topped off with caramel and citrus. Good length and balance overall.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent Pack. Pours a rich amber orange with light head. A mix of floral and passionfruit mark the aroma. The flavours reveal malt and caramel with some citrus and pine lift on the mid-palate and bitterness to finish. Long and balanced flavours overall. Interesting style.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent Pack. Pours pale amber gold with a light head. Fresh fruity aromas including orange, caramel and hints of pine. Rich malty flavours and a mix of caramel and wheat. Interesting and a little different.

330mL bottle, Beerbud Advent pack. Dark chocolate brown with short foamy head. Lifted caramel, brown sugar and coffee aromas. Long soft palate, more coffee and caramel together with hazelnut. Slightly soapy, soft gentle finish. Decent style and flavour.

375mL can. Poured pale gold with a white foamy head and light carbonation. Fresh summery aromas in the glass, with touches of tropical fruits, pineapple and passionfruit. Palate more restrained, light and crisp with subtle citrus bitterness to finish. Light n easy.
330 mL, BeerBud Advent pack. Pours bright amber orange with fine carbonation and a light head. Attractive fresh fruity malty aroma. Mildly flavoured palate, easy drinking but finishes a little short.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent pack. Pours pale amber with a fine head. Fresh citrus and pine aromas, followed by a pronounced malty palate, with nicely weighted bitterness adding character and complexity. Very drinkable.

330mL bottle, BeerBud Advent Pack. Pours pale straw/gold with substantial head. Great zingy aroma, orange, spice (mace) and malted caramel. Complex zesty flavours, a little more banana, buttery, wheaty and a spicy zing. A worthy tipple.

330mL bottle. Pours a deep opaque colour with brown foamy head. Coffee, toffee and smoky bacon aromas, followed by more of the same plus a distinct chocolate brownie flavour. Thoroughly enjoyed it. Great cool weather drinking.
beer_name: Little Creatures Return of The Dread

review_blob: 500ml bottle. Rich brown ale with modest head. Delightful aromas of malt, dark chocolate and caramel. Richly flavoured, multi-layered palate with nutmeg, caramel and spice, slightly sweet finish. Gosh!
Bright amber orange. fine bead, light head. Fresh hoppy aroma, pine, resin and citrus. Great palate, broad malty flavours with pine and lemon, a hit of bitterness to finish. Nice work.
beer_name: Hop Nation The Fiend Australian IPA

review_blob: 330ml bottle. Ive tried different batches from different suppliers and still dont get this. Pours pale orange amber but with minimal carbonation and a rapidly disappearing head. Pleasant hoppy, grassy nose with some malt. Orange and banana hints on palate with a slightly sulphuric sort of mid-palate and little flavour overall. I was expecting much more.
